But this went far beyond the boundaries of a normal lawyer-client relationship.
It was as much as possible a deterrent to police investigations, allowing them to continue their criminal activities.
Mr Ditta has thus brought his profession into disrepute.
He was too close to certain clients, especially Scarborough, and he allowed his independence to be compromised.
