Mohammed Morsi is sworn in, but his day of triumph should not mean the end of political disputes in Egypt.
Islamist Mohammed Morsi promised a "new Egypt" when he was sworn in as the country's first freely elected president, succeeding Hosni Mubarak, who had been ousted 16 months earlier.
