Mocked as an uncharismatic "spare wheel" of the Brotherhood, his personal prestige has grown since his victory and a speech on Friday in which he presented himself as not only the candidate of the Islamists but of all those who wanted to complete the efforts of the 2011 uprising against authoritarian Mubarak.
